word: lake clark national park and preserve

uk: ˌleɪk klɑːk ˌnæʃ.ən.əl pɑːk ən prɪˈzɜːv
us: ˌleɪk klɑːrk ˌnæʃ.ən.əl pɑːrk ən prɪˈzɜːv

body_content.explanation: a national park (= a large area of land protected by the government because of its natural beauty or because it has a special history) in the US state of Alaska:
examples: About 100 miles to the north of the Katmai Park boundary, Chinitna Bay sits on the fringe of Lake Clark National Park and Preserve.
I am currently a geologist-in-the-park at Lake Clark National Park and Preserve in southern Alaska.
